<h2>What is it?</h2>

<p>Ockley is a simple web-based editor for Force.com Apex and Visualforce.
    It aspires to be the textpad/notepad of Force.com development tools.
</p>
<p>It looks like this:<p>
<img src="images/ockley.png" alt="a small pic of ockley in action">

<h2>Why do I care?</h2>
<p>
    Maybe you do and maybe you don't.

    <ul>
        <li>Do you work on the <a href="http://www.salesforce.com/platform/" alt="Force.com platform">Force.com platform</a>?</li>
        <li>Are you interested in alternatives to the Eclipse based <a href="http://wiki.developerforce.com/index.php/Force.com_IDE" alt="Force.com IDE">Force.com IDE</a>?</li>
        <li>Ockley is open-source. You can <a href="https://github.com/mattpage/Ockley" alt="github link">change it</a> if you want to!</li>
    </ul>

</p>

